From: Sergio Lopez <slp@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Oct 2020 11:31:56 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] krun: Initialize addr_vsock in libkip_listen

Otherwise vsock_addr_cast() may fail.

Signed-off-by: Sergio Lopez <slp@redhat.com>
---
 net/socket.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/socket.c b/net/socket.c
index 298fadcb0fce..4c44f495a56c 100644
--- a/net/socket.c
+++ b/net/socket.c
@@ -1709,6 +1709,7 @@ static void libkip_listen(struct socket *sock, int backlog)
 		if (err < 0)
 			return;
 
+		memset(&addr_vsock, 0, sizeof(addr_vsock));
 		addr_vsock.svm_family = AF_VSOCK;
 		addr_vsock.svm_cid = VMADDR_CID_ANY;
 		addr_vsock.svm_port = VMADDR_PORT_ANY;
